            {
                "type": "advice",
                "title": "Hyponatraemia and antidepressant therapy",
                "textContent": "Hyponatraemia (usually in the elderly and possibly due to inappropriate secretion of antidiuretic hormone) has been associated with all types of antidepressants. Hyponatraemia should be considered in all patients who develop drowsiness, confusion, or convulsions while taking an antidepressant.",
